POSITION:Software Developer 1 
Job Description
Design and develop software applications and programs that support Costco Logistics warehouses and Call Centers. Evaluate and a ddress support problems reported by customers, team members, and suppliers. Prepare detailed speci fi cations that support functional and technical requirements. Interact with other developers, operations, Product Owners, and Business Solutions Analysts to ensure that technical solutions support business needs. Create and maintain documentation standards. Participate in requirements gathering sessions to support operational and/or reporting utilization in Costco Logistics fi eld operations. Leverage education and professional experience to work on software features under a code of supervision. Evaluate and provide recommendations on permanent software changes to solve issues. Develop and maintain partnerships with Service Desk to ensure quality service and support .
Minimum Job Requirements
 Education: Bachelor’s or foreign equivalent degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Technology, or a related field.
 Experience: Six months of software development experience in:
 JavaScript ES6;
 HyperText Markup Language ;
 Cascading Style Sheets ;
 React and Redux;
 Jest and Jenkins;
 Microservice architecture;
 MySQL relational database; and
 AWS and/or Azure cloud computing technologies and services
Name of Employer:Costco Wholesale Corporation
Position location:Schaumburg, IL
Salary Range:$100,000 to $110,000 per year
40 hours per week, 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., M-F
Benefits: We offer a comprehensive package of benefits including paid time off, health benefits - medical/dental/vision/hearing aid/pharmacy/behavioral health/employee assistance, health care reimbursement account, dependent care assistance plan, short-term disability and long-term disability insurance, AD&D insurance, life insurance, 401(k), stock purchase plan to eligible employees.

